Despite criticism of the fact that the main roles are played by actors Americans, South Africans say that the new film of Hollywood - will explain to the world a lot about the country, its fighting and victories.
The history of sport, relations between races and Nelson Mandela.
Morgan Freeman, American actor rewarded the Oscars, embodies the film on the life of Nelson Mandela, tireless fighter against the racist apartheid regime in South Africa and first black president.
Freeman said, that this is a Mandela aged 91 who asked her to embody in the film.
Matt Damon plays another role.
I told him: "if I must embody, I should be able to see you personally..
The actor seventy-two years old who was awarded a prize for his role in the drama limited Dollar Baby of Clint Eastwood located in the middle of boxing has, for example, embodied the leader of a movement against slavery itself become a slave, a fictional US president, even God in the film Evan Almighty but never someone still alive and also important for so many people that is Mandela.
The former South African statesman was jailed for 27 years for his hard work in favour of the end of apartheid in South Africa.
He was released in 1990 and became president of the country for four years.
In 1993 he was awarded the Nobel Peace Prize.
Invictus is a Latin word meaning unbeaten and it is the title of a poem by the English author William Ernest Henley published in 1875.
The challenge was to speak.
The film tells The true story of The joint efforts of Nelson Mandela and The captain of The South African rugby team François to unify The country. The newly elected President Mandela knows that his country Resteencore and still divided racially and economically after apartheid.
It is sure to unite his people through sport and decides to unite the rugby players who are among the outsiders in the world ranking.
The South African team will eventually move in World Cup in 1995.
Freeman has worked for a few years to bring the history of Mandela on screen.
I had no other purpose if not play this role to bring the more than reality, "said freeman.
The biggest challenge for me it was, of course, talk like him
The actor said that if he and the international policy were in the same region, it would have tried to meet Mandela, dinner with him, to be behind the scenes before his speech.
The most important thing for him was to shake hands.
I realized that when I shake hands with you, I recover your energy, it is transmitted and I had the impression of how you feel, he said.
It is important for me to try to become another person.
Matt Damon plays in the film François Pienaar, the captain of a National Rugby team in which there is a majority of white players.
The actor said he had six months to prepare for a role in the harsh environment of rugby.
For him, his first meeting with Pienaar at his home was a great surprise.
I remember when I come to the door of the house, I opened and the first thing I said to Francois Pienaar was:' I have the air much greater in the film ".
Despite the differences between the real actors and models, Invictus under the leadership of the director Eastwood received positive notices and there is even talk of ambitions for the Oscars.
