In the evaluations of films on the site rottentomatoes.com, Invictus received 76 percent of positive feedback.
The mystery of the aura in Norway is resolved: the Russian tested a rocket
There has been a strange light phenomenon of unknown origin over Norway.
The Russian Ministry of Defence has recognized that yesterday have tested a rocket intercontinental ballistic missile near the Norwegian border.
The launch has yet been a failure and the type "bulava missile" which was originally to be the pride of the Russian army is gradually becoming the nightmare of Russian generals and Prime Minister Vladimir putin.
His presence repeated tests of the rocket has not had the desired effect on the success of test flights.
Most of the time, Bulava has not disappeared, or it is damaged in flight.
The Russian newspapers speak of "Bulava" as the "missile which do not steal"
A missile that is not
This 13th test took place at the beginning normally.
It is only at the end of the flight that there was further damage on the apparatus.
This is clearly the engine of the third floor of the rocket that exploded.
This time, "Bulava" has disappeared from the nuclear submarine Dmitrij Donskij which was sailing under the surface of the White Sea.
This type of missile can be fired from a moving boat and submerged
That is why the mysterious light above Norway caused by an unidentified flying object precisely the has likely been a bulava "flawed.
The rest, the Norwegians have not doubted a moment that it is a Russian rocket.
The generals argue that this time, we cannot talk absolutely failure.
The first two floors of the rocket have resisted and damage was confined to the third.
In previous cases, the engines have been failures on the first floor.
Even if no test launches went smoothly, the direction of the Ministry of Defence considers that only six out of thirteen have been failures.
The success rate of almost 50 per cent fills the general optimism and they say is always a day "Bulava'fly without problems and that it will even ten nuclear cores hypersoniques a total weight of 1.15 tonnes.
