According to the new schedules of the ČD there will be fewer trains for the same charges.
The czech Railways will remove or limit from 13 December some express trains or regional less responsible and instead would increase other.
The total coverage of transport fall on the day of entry into force of the new schedules of two percent compared to today.
Most of the charges will not change, including the basic rates and reduced fare.
For example, the inhabitants of the Ostrava region which will have more routes to the capital, the Railways will add a rowing.
On the contrary, an Express will cease to serve Bratislava.
There will also be less fast trains on the line Prague - Písek - České Budějovice, the direct line Prague - Letohrad will be drastically reduced.
At the regional level, the largest decrease in transportation for the region of Hradec Králové of eight percent in total, Prague and its environs can increase.
Two night trains on the line Prague - Tábor - České Budějovice are also cancelled and the movement of some express trains on the line Prague - Písek - České Budějovice is reduced to only a few days in the week.
Among the most sweeping changes, we can see the introduction of a new direct line of Milovice in prague: for the moment the inhabitants of Milovice must change to Lysá nad labem.
It is for the fifteenth line of commuter system, including the opening is possible thanks to the completion of the electrification of the line between Lysá nad Labem and Milovice.
The lines distant to the capital will have their final destination at the main railway station in Prague (Praha Hlavní nádraží).
The ČD will introduce more lines SC Pendolino between Prague and Ostrava and trains to Šumperk / Jeseník will leave by intervals of two hours.
Travellers can no longer take the Pendolino up in Bratislava on 13 December.
The bill this year for regional railways: 200 million kronor.
The express trains are ordered and paid by The department of transportation and The Railways will next year in all four billion kronor to visible, The same amount as this year. The regional trains are controlled by The regions who will pay for their by a total of eight billion next year, knowing that The state will participate to The tune of almost three billion.
This year the regional trains are 200 million more expensive.
The railways have newly signed a contract for ten years, until now the duration was always a year.
The Railways appreciate the system, which also explains that they have not used a price increase of the vast majority of tickets.
The changes will affect only tickets a day ČD Net and the Internet eLiška.
For travellers without a map of reduction, the price of ČD Net increase of 450 to 600 crowns.
The price of eLiška newly will depend on the journey, whereas previously it was valid between the towns of a region to choice and was at a single rate of 160 crowns.
The Filipino rebels still retain more than 50 people, children have been released
The rebels have kidnapped today 75 people in the southern Philippines, including some pupils in primary school and their teachers.
It is the AFP Agency informed, but who spoke to the origin of 65 hostages only.
The 17 children were released after eight hours, as well as a teacher.
The hijacking took place in the province of Agusan del sur.
It is reported that about 19 rebels have used hostages as human shields during a flight to the police.
The local negotiators are trying to find an agreement for the release of the remaining hostages.
According to the AFP Agency, the rebels belong to the New People's Army (NPA), which is the armed wing of the Communist Party of the Philippines (CPP).
According to the AFP agency, the police initially pursued the kidnappers following violence caused a settling of accounts between two family clans.
Martial law was declared in the province of Maguindanao in the southern Philippines because of a recent massacre in which 57 people were killed.
Among the victims of the massacre of 23 November linked to the elections of the administration of the Governor there avait30 journalists.
The governor of the province of the southern Philippines was arrested on suspicion of involvement in the massacre, as well as his father Andal Ampatuan, patriarch of the lineage of influential Ampatuan.
The island of Mindanao also includes Muslim separatists.
They have renewed peace talks with the Philippine government Tuesday.
