A processor worth tens of millions of kronor in flames in the area of Louny
A fire has engulfed in the morning a processor of society Čeps distribution centre near the municipality of Výškov na Lounsku.
According to Lukáš marvan, spokesman of the Ústí, there are six units that operate on the fire.
They were originally leave the processor is consumer, but they have reviewed their opinion and off the fire with a mixture of water, foam and a special substance.
The cause is a technical failure, an internal short circuit of the processor.
No one was injured, according to the spokesman of the society Pavla Mandátova the incident does not endanger the safe operation of the entire transmission.
The damage is estimated at tens of millions of kronor, the exact figure will be known once the fire extinguished.
According to Mandátova, the processor destroyed will be replaced by a new one.
She added that in ten years of activity, the society Čeps has experienced anything similar and that such incidents are isolated.
The power supplies were not interrupted, said the spokesman for the Society for the north Bohemia Soňa Holingerova Hendrychova, the functioning of homes, government and industry has not been influenced by the fire station.
A.s. Čeps is the exclusive operator on the Czech territory sets of transmission and power lines of 400 kV and 220 kV.
It maintains, upgrades and develops 39 distribution with 67 processors transferring electric power since the sets of transport for distribution and a length of lines tracing 4339 kilometres.
