The prison guards' unions called Friday for "general mobilization" to demand the payment by the end of year holidays bonuses and overtime which payment has been deferred to January for budgetary reasons.
Fo-pénitentiaire (2 th kgeu supervisors) has asked the personnel who will not be in service to demonstrate Tuesday morning before the prisons and the "block", to "denounce the theft of their due."
The CGT-pénitentiaire (3rd of the profession) calls on them to "meet in general assemblies in different prisons for strong mobilization", saying "shameful and unacceptable" the non-payment in December of' overtime, bonuses for night, Sundays and holidays "in October.
