Case Liliane Bettencourt: François-Marie Banier will be tried for abuse of weakness
The court in Nanterre decided Friday to assess the artist François-Marie Banier to determine if, as in accuses the daughter of the billionaire Liliane Bettencourt, it has benefited from a state of the weakness of the 80-year-old to rob a part of his fortune.
The photographer 62 years, known for his photos of stars, will be judged on the 15 and 16 April 2010 for abuse of weakness, an offence punishable by a maximum penalty of three years in prison and 375,000 euros in fines.
This decision means that there will be a trial in this case worthy of a saga on one of the richest families of france, in which a mother and daughter are squabbling while taking the reins of the empire of cosmetics oréal.
But the 15th Criminal Chamber also ordered that a medical expertise of Liliane Bettencourt, aged 87 years, should be waged collectively by three doctors.
The heir and a major shareholder in L'Oréal has always refused to submit to such a review, at least not in the conditions proposed by the prosecution of Nanterre during the investigation.
The doctors named Friday to submit a report before 10 March 2010 by saying, especially if Liliane Bettencourt could find themselves in the state of weakness and what periods.
I think it will.
I'm going to talk, "said at the end of the hearing, counsel for Mrs Bettencourt, Georges Kiejman.
For its part, counsel for Françoise Bettencourt-Meyers, I Olivier Metzner, welcomed the decision of the court.
This is excellent news (...) The expertise will show that he (Mr Banier) has manipulated this elderly lady that we must protect, he said.
For two years, the only daughter of Liliane Bettencourt has committed criminal proceedings against François-Marie Banier, photographer and artist, which it accuses of having benefited for years from the weakness of his mother to obtain one billion euros in donations, in the form of cheques, contracts of life insurance or tables.
For its part, Liliane Bettencourt has always denied having been manipulated by the photographer, as an old friend.
While the court should examine the admissibility of the action taken by Ms. Bettencourt-Meyers, arguments from lawyers have sometimes turned into a large family unpacking Friday.
Thus, counsel Liliane Bettencourt has reported three letters sent by his client (in 1999, 2003 and 2005) to his notary, in which she said wary of the husband of Françoise Bettencourt-Meyers.
In the letter dated 2003, Liliane Bettencourt added, according to the lawyer: "could you explain to my daughter that I wrote to Banier once, twice a day for 15 years.
Françoise, I have never been able to speak to him since his marriage ".
For its part, the prosecutor in Nanterre again suggested that the complainant was not admissible to act, especially as a juvenile judge has refused in recent days to allow its application to open a judicial procedure of protection for his mother.
Liliane Bettencourt "has full capacity to act, it is not under protection and has no guardian.
No one else has to act in his place, "said the representative of the public prosecutor, Marie-Chrsitine Daubigney.
The court has finally decided that it would decide once the trial will be held on the admissibility of Ms. Bettencourt-Meyers.
Managerial Revolution or end of the economic intelligence?
If nothing changes in the governance of large French companies, our struggle for the development of the economic intelligence will be pointless...
For more than a decade, the attitude of the management of large companies in relation to its employees, recalls the position of vis-à-vis consumers before the revolution marketing: it is to join the staff to "values" defined above as it was once, to dictate to consumers of products devised by the technicians of the plant.
By putting the customer at the heart of the company, revolution marketing has presented the strategies of conquest of markets to the place... although the authoritarian temptation to impose products disconnected factors of preferences populations return regularly!
A demobilization of employees can lead to a deadly demoralisation.
The suicides at France Telecom, PSA and Renault are only the tip of a much more general phenomenon which affects.
This demobilization seriously undermines the development of all intellectual functions of the company, including R&D and, more importantly, the economic intelligence.
Indeed, the IE "requires of all stakeholders (...) a proactive approach and a prospective vision"; it requires a commitment on the part of employees that the authoritarian management completely.
That is why we call for a managerial revolution that would put the staff at the centre of concerns of the company as well as the client.
The relative opinion surveys
The investigation of domestic opinion – as the questionnaire submitted by Orange to its salariés- will encourage this revolution in the managerial?
Unfortunately, I am afraid not.
- first because I could see that, faced with a new situation, any structure in the end, after many detours, priority … what it has always done.
- Secondly, because the authoritarianism one of the pathologies of increases in proportion to the importance of its own failures.
- Finally, because most of the leaders have a simplistic view of human behaviour.
From the major engineering schools, they have a mechanistic interpretation of psychology.
They adopt, by intellectual comfort, the old theory Behavioriste, recently revived by the "Neuroscience" and widely disseminated, without their knowledge, by the institutes and the media.
Thus, by suggesting that it is possible to handle "levers" (sic) of the commitment of executives, a recent survey by Ipsos published in Le Figaro fr confirms she leaders in a mechanistic governance posture, unsuited to today's world.
Identify and measure the factors
On the contrary, the managerial revolution necessary for the proper functioning of modern enterprises, to adopt a finalist vision of human behaviour.
It is to integrate, in any reasoning or practice of governance, a fundamental observation: for employees, the commitment to the company is possible only if it is clear as a means to achieve some of their dreams, their ambitions, their projects.
Currently, only studies from the Analysis motifonctionnelle adopt this conception of the motivations of employees.
These studies have shown that they consider their company based on a predetermined doxa which allows them, through their image of the company, to assess what it offers to achieve their life projects.
Thanks to the identification and the extent of these factors of mobilization, business leaders can control, predict and anticipate their "social performance" and submit their management of human resources in the area. "
They create a breeding ground for joint development of a robust and effective economic intelligence.
