Thanks to this evidence of journalistic independence, Schächter was able to propose for the position of editor without losing face, as well as the board of directors could elect without being suspects to place as a partisan politics.
In the representations of the parties, Frey is classified liberal left.
Cleaning up university
Partial success for students: after a year of educational strike the Ministers of Education and Cultural Affairs of the Länder decide to be more conciliatory: at a meeting between Ministers and delegates to the conference of presidents, an agreement has been developed that the working conditions of students Bachelor or Master should be improved.
In the future, students should be able to overcome their studies.
They particularly accordpour lighten the burden of reviews: a single review should help to close the study module.
In addition, the workload will be Reconsidée to ensure "realistic and acceptable proportions".
The political authorities and higher education institutions wish to facilitate the recognition of examinations between universities and abroad.
The Länder are also committed to organise common structural requirements more flexible for the Bachelor and master.
At the regional level, there should be no regulation of a land to another.
Less reviews
Since the beginning of student protests in June, the Minister of Education of the Länder and the university presidents have repeatedly to mouth the buzzword: "étudiabilité."
But for the first time, this expression seems to take a practical meaning.
The accreditation council decided to significantly reduce the number of some reviews: "each module should normally be concluded by a single review," read in a document of 30 pages of future conditions for admission to graduate.
Reinhold Grimm, President of the accreditation council said that by significantly reducing the burden of reviews should be able to stop the abuses, which significantly the étudiabilité.
The "étudiabilité" should also be, in the future, the decisive criterion of the organization of studies.
The modules as substance must be examined carefully to see if we cannot avoid this smothering sensation that you feel sometimes in the choice of courses.
Hamburg / Berlin - According to the latest knowledge in RAID on Kunduz, the opposition believes that the Minister of defence Karl-Theodor zu Guttenberg (CSU) is guilty of deliberate deception.
Students should "have the opportunity and the flexibility to allow and encourage the personal initiative".
The new regulation will affect access to new graduate but will also be adapted to the existing cycles.
These cycles must be re-certified "every 5 years, which means, however, that it is only by 2015 that all cycles have been reviewed.
There are 10 of accreditation agencies throughout the federal territory which depend on the Accreditation Council created by the Länder.
In october, the Ministers of Education had exerted some pressure on the Länder to weigh on the agencies so that the programmes are not too busy and the regime of not too strict.
In some Länder, universities and colleges specialized have already agreed with their regional departments to take appropriate measures.
The Rhineland-Palatinate is so far the only Land to have agreed to grant more resources to the development of the Bologna process.
With these funds, universities must organize programs tutorielset strengthen educational guidance offices and the offices of reviews and the service of International Relations
The Länder and universities provide a budget of EUR 10 million.
In early 2010, the government wants to submit to Parliament an amendment to the law on higher education institutions.
As a result, there will be no more one consideration to complete his studies.
The organization of studies should be more flexible, more must be able to ensure the recognition of transcripts of other institutions of higher education and access to the Master must be simplified.
By the end of next year, the étudiabilité "of all university review.
Last Thursday, the government and the opposition have again discussed the issue of study conditions in the country.
The décisionsont been appreciated but criticisms have been heard.
The Federal President of the student union Socialist indicated that it would like the organization of educational policy does not happen again in the future "behind closed doors" of Ministers and heads of universities.
