More than a footnote on Herta Müller
It is by these words "Arrival in Germany and it is beautiful, almost more control..." that begins the poet Werner Söllner, in which he dealt with in snippets of sentences disturbing, the experiences of a dissident arrived in Germany who won freedom but has lost at the same time its linguistic territory.
Werner Söllner, born in 1951 in Romania, was first professor of German and English in Bucharest and, subsequently, director of collection in a publishing house for youth before moving to Frankfurt am Main.
Söllner received various literary prizes; in 1993 he was the chair very popular poetry of the Goethe University in Frankfurt and since 2002 it is director of the Forum of Literature of Hesse to the house of artist of Mousonturm in Frankfurt.
He has done a lot of him in circles not literary last tuesday, at a conference in munich, whose theme was "the German literature in Romania in the mirror and the distorting mirror of your files securitate".
Visibly upset and embarrassed, Söllner made a statement in which he acknowledged to his fellow writers Germano-roumains as Richard Wagner, William Totok, Franz Hodjak, and Helmuth Frauendorfer that he had worked as an informer for the Securitate political police.
Söllner received in 1989 the price of the German language together with some of the participants.
Tests began in 1971.
I am, "concludes söllner so someone who has not been able to resist auxessais intimidation of the Securitate."
The poet Werner Söllner is the informant Walter (Im Walter).
Almost simultaneously with the Honoration of the Nobel Prize for Herta Müller and his literary copies with the mechanisms of power of the dictatorship, the literary scene is shaken and in particular the community of German authors from Romania, in a case that clearly shows the abyss and of a political system based on police surveillance and espionage.
Werner Söllner is, as far as we can tell from the current knowledge, not only guilty but also victim.
In his own dossier Securitate, Im Walter has played a role, the specialist literature Michael Markel after the confession of Söllner and it refers to the positive influence of Im Walter, who had intervened in his favour.
"It had been drawn from all the difficult situations at the time," according to Markel.
Markel has felt the need Moralde make this comment.
The form in which Söllner made his statement and before the public was unexpected, however the admission of a former dissident its cooperation with the Romanian Intelligence Service is in fact, not so surprising.
Germany is a reserve for the spies of the Securitate had already written Herta Müller in July in the journal "Die Zeit, having read the 914 pages of his own case.
It can be assumed that the victims have made speculation and may have guessed what real names were hiding last names of borrowing sorin, Voicu and walter.
Unlike Germany where the consultation of the Stasi files is a reliable process, the attitude to the legacy of the files of the Securitate is still very confused.
A systematic clarification has been repeatedly frustrated and slowed in the past.
It was only in 1999 that a national council corresponding to the institution Birthler was created to work to the assimilation of the Securitate Archives (CNSAS) but the restitution of files rather has dragged on since.
Since 2005 there is a law that defines the management of archives.
The influence of former members of the Securitate in Romania is still very great, is confirmed by an interview with a former head of the Securitate of Temesvar which, after the announcement of the award of the Nobel Prize to Herta Müller, expressed in a very dismissive of the winner.
She had a psychosis, and ultimately it had questioned only once.
The infamy of power to speak here, without any gene, under the guise of freedom of expression.
Certainly, many issues are associated with the case Söllner as happens so often in a context of guilt.
Why now? which has been robbed? The prudent reaction of listeners, The admission of söllner, gives us hope that The result of this chapter will be defined more by a thirst for knowledge that by accusations and a sense of shame.
On the genesis of the work of Herta müller, who received the Nobel prize yesterday, is more than a footnote.
