75% of working mothers have had problems because of their maternity
Discrimination at work has increased in recent years, especially for women of younger generations who want to be mothers.
This is what the study "fertility and career women in spain," conducted by the CSIC in collaboration with the Instituto de la mujer.
The survey, conducted on 9 737 women aged 15 to 75 years, leaves no room for doubt: 75% of working mothers saw their careers because of motherhood.
The study indicates that there are many differences concerning the beginning of life as a couple and the number of children, if the woman works or not and the type of job.
Those who do not work outside the home, working part-time or have a less stable, earlier couple, have their first pregnancy earlier and have more children.
In contrast, women with stable employment, mainly in the public sector, pushing the entry in the conjugal life and the first pregnancy, and have fewer children.
The women between 35 and 49 years with a fixed work have their first child, on average, 3.7 years after being installed in couple. This figure rises to 4.1 among those working in the public sector. "These data show that women with a stable employment needed more time in their lives for it, which led them to reject the union and the arrival of children.
In addition, the type of employment exercised influence largely motherhood, but less the start date of common life, "explains the researcher of the CSIC Margarita Delgado.
The level of education is another factor that widening the gap in the age of marriage for women and their first child.
According to the survey, the higher the level of training, the more they marry and have their first child later.
The difference is also among women of the same generation.
For example, in the group between 35 and 49 years, those who have made elementary and higher education were mothers for the first time to 25.1 and 32.1 years on average.
"Another is also among women, according to their level of education.
While those who have studies elementary marry and have their first child before finding stable employment, those with higher average level studies or reverse this programme and give priority to the achievement of a stable work as a precondition to marriage and the arrival of a child, "said mrs delgado.
