On Joseph conrad: "on his grave were engraved to spenser:" Sleep after the effort, / after the storm the port, / the rest after the war, / after life, tired death ears. "
On Virginia wolf: "in its baggage she was carrying also depressions.
Her husband accepted very normally she told him that Edward VII the between Azalées or that the birds singing in Greek.
