A cowardly aggression
Last week, my mother, who was about 70 years old, was walking in our neighbourhood of the city of Fuenlabrada, when a group of young people between 15 and 18 years spent beside it and our dog, a sang-mélé, saved from the APS and not weighing more than six pounds, and without saying a word, they both assenèrent kicking the dog who left seriously injured.
Our indignation is immense because we do not see what is a funny to attack a free small animal defence which, moreover, was on a leash.
Add to this the indignation of a woman who was walking quietly and that, when she injuria these individuals, came to fear for their physical integrity, as a énergumène which attack an animal is capable of doing the same thing to a woman, a child, an old man and, ultimately, any person lower than him.
The episode took place at around 5 p.m., Tuesday as another, in a normally quiet neighbourhood.
The dog has Gémi throughout the day.
We obviously complained to the police station in the district although we doubt that this serves to much and not to touch the sensitivities, we just want to clarify that the cowardly murderers were Spanish.
The outrage has led us to denounce this fact.
We do not understand what is happening in the youth so that they find amusing to mistreat a defenceless animal gives us free of affection, friendship and keeps us company.
We do not know where is the good education and respect for animals and people.
Michelin and Fesvial, sets for helmet
The tyre manufacturer Michelin, in collaboration with the Spanish Foundation for Road Safety (Fesvial), has launched a campaign to encourage the use of helmets, mainly among motorcyclists, like said today the two structures.
This initiative aims to raise awareness of the importance of helmets, since it is the only element of protection to prevent injuries to the head, or even death, in the event of an accident with two wheels.
Michelin said that the campaign was in line with his commitment to road safety, which "goes beyond the design and manufacture of products still safer" and said it contributed to this objective by other actions to educational and informative nature.
This new campaign for encouragement of helmets in two wheels, under the motto "to be or not to be", will include a first phase during which posters will be distributed in more than 500 garages of motorcycles, in order to ensure the widest dissemination.
Finally, Michelin has stressed that the road safety "is a constant concern" for the company, because as a manufacturer of tyres for two-wheeled vehicles, one of its main objectives is to develop products safe.
The sale of light commercial vehicles is
After nearly two years, the market for light commercial vehicles is beginning to see a little light at the end of the tunnel.
The 9 425 vehicles registered in November in Spain represent an increase of 12.6% compared to 2008 and, more importantly, they represent the first increase after 22 consecutive months of decline, according to figures from the employers' organisation Anfac and of Ganvam manufacturers, dealers.
However, we need to qualify the good news since the reference to the comparison, the month of November 2008, was particularly bad, with a 60% decrease compared to the previous year.
As a result, despite the rebound last month, registrations accumulated during the 11 months are 40% below those of the previous year.
Since January, if you add up all vehicles in the category of light commercial vehicles (derived from passenger cars, pickups, vans, light vans and trucks to lightweight chassis) 95 have been sold.
The dark clouds that affect their application have not dispelled. indeed, although they are also purchased by individuals, most purchases are made by small or medium-sized enterprises, which pay in almost 100% of cases through an external funding.
Thus, in addition to the restrictions involved by limiting bank loans, we must add other factors such as the increase in the unemployment rate or the persistence of the poor economic climate.
Faced with this situation and unlike cars, aid to the purchase of the 2000E have little used.
Addition to individuals, the self-employed and SMEs wishing to acquire a light commercial vehicle of less than 3.5 tonnes with a level of Co2 emissions which does not exceed 160 grams per kilometre, can also benefit, but the number of operations speaks for itself.
Yesterday, in Ganvam recalled again the need for the administration to attach special attention to these vehicles and also to industrial vehicles (trucks and buses).
The dealers association provides a year 2010 similar to that end, for which she calculates a drop in sales (passenger vehicles and 4x4) of 19%.
The emergency braking is now mandatory
As has occurred with the anti-lock brakes ABS and as it will take place with the ESP stability control, the system of emergency brakes will be a compulsory element on European cars.
They are already mandatory on passenger cars and light commercial vehicles newly registered, while in the rest of the vehicles a waiting period was set up at the end of February 2011.
The measure, imposed by the European Union, aims to strengthen the protection of pedestrians, even if, in its mode of action, it can also help prevent many rear shocks.
The assistant emergency braking is increasing pressure on the brakes in urgent cases detected by the system through the kick given by the driver.
But it does not always maintained the pressure until the end.
According to a study conducted by the manufacturer of components for cars bosch, a third of the drivers involved in an accident could not rely on the brakes before the collision, and half of them had not benefited from its full force.
Up to 1,100
The intervention of the aid, Revancha, requires the maximum brake system, reducing the distance that the car needs to stop.
According to a study of the eu, if all cars were equipped with such elements, up to 1,100 fatal accidents in which pedestrians are involved could be avoided each year.
This reduction would be even more important with the popularization of so-called intelligent emergency braking systems: it calculates that a disaster on four with injured would be avoided.
In this case, the vehicle is equipped with a system which, thanks to a radar or a camera detects obstacles and warns the driver, in addition to act slightly on the brakes.
If the driver reacts, it aid by increasing the pressure on the pedal, if necessary.
If it does not react, and although the collision is inevitable, the device carries the maximum effort on the brakes to minimize the damage.
