At the wheel of the Porsche Boxster Spyder
To design their last and valuable jewelry, engineers are parties of the Porsche Boxster S and succeeded to the thinning of nothing less than 80 kilos, leaving the balance to only 1 275 kilograms.
This has led to happen, first, the roof automatic which has been replaced by a roof bâché manual, capable of delivering 21 kilos, to employ aluminum doors as those of the gt3, other 15 kilos of less, to remove the air conditioner, 13 kilos, to reduce the tank of petrol from 64 to 54 litres, 7 kilos of earned, to mount bacquets sport, still 12 kilos, and with tyres light of 19 inches, five kilos.
Finally, they have relinquished the audio system cdr-30, earning six other kilograms and have replaced the poignéesdes doors by the wrists in tissues, saving the kilo remaining.
Although the model also exists with the box PDK double clutch, the test was carried out on a model to manual transmission of six speeds, mainly on secondary roads in California, in the mountains, with particularly tortuous turns.
His behaviour cannot be described as beyond reproach.
The decrease in weight does not prevent the car to drive on the ground with aplomb.
On the contrary: it was a long time that we had not tested a model as small and light which, at the same time, guarantee security in the turns, including at high speed.
It is a small athlete, able to heat its Musclesà small speed for as long as necessary, until we ask him to sprinter, to recover and grow again its engine...
It is out what we wanted. Through his leadership, also communicative as specified, the car will do what will our hands on the steering wheel.
And it will do so with surgical precision.
Its engine
The sound of his BOXER V6, with 320 horses (10 more than the Boxster S) is particularly successful and can be strengthened with the Option "sport" or through a system that changes the roar of the engine, already used on the Panamera.
The ability of acceleration is brutal, with the ruling or success.
The suspensions are firm, but not harsh or uncomfortable.
The paving of roads that we have travelled with the Boyxster Spyder was quite damaged, but the car was well managed potholes.
The electronic assistants were barely act of presence throughout the journey, while on some turns we found ice in the morning and gravel, later in the morning.
Ultimately, a car Ultralégère, more entertaining to drive and that is much more than a simple change of the Boxster S.
The car will be put on sale in February 2010, at a price of 70 831 euros.
