How much should you be paid according to your Facebook profile?
Users of Facebook may know the salary they deserve depending on their profile, thanks to a new application of trovit, the search engine with the largest number of real estate ads, employment and vehicles in spain.
The tool "How should you be paid?" calculates the salaries of users from more than 140 000 job opportunities available Trovit in Spain, from a form available on Facebook, where you have to register your profession, your years of experience, your age and the city where you want to work.
For a week that the application works, the search engine has detected that, as a general rule, the Spanish worker "feels poorly paid," said in a statement the head of Trovit products, Albert Ribera.
According to the data available Trovità from its search engines in the United Kingdom and France, the Spanish are the least well paid.
A British computer programmer collects 45 226 euros annual gross and a french, 31 059, while a Spanish receives eur 24 000.
Similarly, a driver is 34 247 euros annual gross in England, 25 751 in France and 16 420 in Spain.
According to Trovit, the lowest paid in Spain is that of server, with 11 592 Euros annual net, followed by the seller, with 14 725 euros, and that of worker, with 15 667 euros.
The most sought-after jobs on the Internet during the past three months are driver, part-time jobs and social worker.
Brazil sets a date for the departure of Zelaya
The Brazilian government has set a deadline for the stay of Manuel Zelaya in its embassy in Tegucigalpa.
The deposed president will abandon the diplomatic legation no later than January 27, 2010, the date of the official end of its mandate.
Francisco Catunda, chargé d ’ affaires of the Embassy of Brazil in the capital of Honduras, confirmed to TV Globo that "Mel" knows that he must leave the embassy, where he has refugee since 21 September, before that date.
"He is aware that he must leave on 27 january, at the end of its mandate, it must seek another destination."
The chain has also cited the former agent, who confirmed his intention to leave the embassy before the end of the deadline established: "my position is to leave as soon as possible, naturally with the support of the Brazilian government," Zelaya said by telephone.
After the elections of 29 November (during which Porfirio Lobo was elected), Zelaya assured that it would remain in the Embassy of Brazil until January.
However, the same week, he tried to seek refuge in Brazil.
The operation ultimately failed, since Zelaya refused the condition of exiled policy that would impose the de facto government headed by Roberto Micheletti.
Thank you very much
After days roses since last spring, during which the asset inflation was the dominant note on the markets, the uncertainty arises again, which is not surprising since it is their natural state, in an environment where the officials take decisions on a future uncertain by nature.
The remedy used by central banks to stabilise the markets was to monetize the debt by the direct purchase of assets and indirectly by providing abundant liquidity at close to zero, so that financial institutions buy assets to mobilize.
Central banks have already confirmed that the direct purchases of assets were virtually finalized and, without jeopardising their political maverick of liquidity, begin to put a bit of sand in the wheels, as did the ECB, with their award to a year in the next week.
Therefore, investors doubt the ability of the global economy to maintain an economic recovery without measures and we are now seeing a reversal of the reduction of risk premiums.
The volatility of stock markets and business obligations increase again, although they remain very distant from the levels they have reached at the beginning of the year.
The states were forced to socialize the risk private and public debt is affected.
There is a flight to quality and the United States, Japan and Germany have been selected shelters by investors, an increase of differences between the countries of the euro zone and Germany.
Spain has been barely affected by this episode of instability, but then Standard & Poor's threatened a further downward revision of the qualification of the Kingdom of Spain.
On the other hand, a bit of uncertainty is not bad to silence the defenders of moral hazard, trying again to induce a case of awareness among lesresponsables of the global economic policy that had hampered the destructive effects of the restriction of credit on the destruction of the job, whereas what should be done is declaring a new day of Thanksgiving.
However, the situation of Dubai resembles a fight between the tribal sheiks to restore power in the emirates and we have already seen the case of greece.
A government that conceals a public deficit, elections, and a new government who discovers the pot in roses.
Prodi did in Italy after Berlusconi and Socrates in Portugal after Durão Barroso.
It would be perfectly irrational that Ecofin saves Hungary for non respect of its external payments at the beginning of the year and allow a member country of the euro area not to meet its commitments.
What is logical is that the Ecofin has prompted the Greek government to transparency and make its citizens share of the need for extraordinary measures to maintain the stability of its public finances.
If, as we hope, we are faced with an episode of standardization of risk premiums transitional, after some excesses in positions, this would be predictable.
In the case of spain, as our differences of public debt is increasing to the extent of the obligations of European companies, nousn not to worry.
If the European and continued to increase, it would be a risk idiosyncratic Spanish.
The Standard & Poor's is an anecdote. When our indicators estimates are forcing most of the services of studies to anticipate their models of recovery and to revise upwards their forecast for 2011, with the OECD and the European Commission, due to the burden with a Japanese model pourl Spanish economy, it does not much hope for their warning.
Again, this has all the air to provide an excellent opportunity to buy assets Spanish, even if for the moment "caution is the mother safety."
Sectors connected
The chairman of Iberdrola, Ignacio Sánchez Galán, was the first to intervene yesterday, before the subcommittee of the Congress of Deputies, where is discussed these days the energy strategy of Spain for the next two decades.
After his speech, which was followed by the president of Gas Natural-Fenosa, Rafael Villaseca, Mr Galán has outlined for the press that he had spoken to the sub-commission,.
For the president of iberdrola, Spain needs to invest eur 50 000 million until 2020 and 60 000 million between this date and 2030, in cases where nuclear power stations today in operation would remain open.
If this is not the case, the necessary investments do not amount to 60 000 million but to 95.
By contrast, Iberdola considers that for the next decade, investments should not be used to increase production capacity, but the distribution networks and international interconnections.
From 2020, the question is changing, and it will increase the power.
His bet focuses both gas and coal, with mechanisms for recovery of carbon dioxide and, above all, on renewable energy.
In this area, it considers that 18,000 MW of more are needed, with other "energies of support".
Galán, who believes that the bill a sustainable economy that the government has approved is in line with what calls his company, did not wish to attack the royal decree to encourage consumption of national coal, which contradicts the policies to combat global warming.
According to him, there was "a clear long-term bet" in this sense, despite the measures "walk-ins", as qualified the president of Iberdrola.
Anyway, Galán believes that decisions to invest, although they are in the long term, must begin to be taken, because they take some time before reaching maturity and a lucrative stable framework is needed to address them.
