FCC, through its subsidiary Alpine, is adjudiquer the construction of a tunnel of 2.1 miles long for a motorway in Slovenia, for $64.5 million euros.
The Company has obtained this contract a few days after being given the responsibility of the expansion of the tunnel Bosruck (Austria), for a total of 130 million.
Alpine consolidates its experience in the construction of tunnels.
The launch of the site is planned for early 2010 and its implementation will take 32 months.
Sra. Rushmore is adjudiquer advertising of Renfe
Renfe has left the services of advertising and marketing of these two years to the agency Sra. Rushmore, for a budget of around three million euros per year, said the rail operator.
The contract mentioned the possibility of two extensions of 12 months each. sra. Rushmore was chosen from among 16 agencies are presented to tender organised by renfe, of which four were finalists, including TBWA who was responsible for the creativity over the past three years.
From now on, Sra. Rushmore will be responsible for the design and production of campaigns.
A fine of 63 million to France Telecom to curb competition.
The French competition regulator imposed a fine of eur 63 million to France Telecom for its anti-competitive conduct in the Caribbean region in the country.
According to this institution, the operator has limited competition on the fixed and mobile telephony by signing exclusive agreements, tariffs and loyalty programs to consumers in the margins of regulation.
With this sanction, the former French monopoly and state-run company, accumulates more than 450 million euros in fines since 1994, because of the obstacles to its competitors.
The sanction imposed yesterday has been increased because the authority which ensures competition considers that France Telecom has committed similar offences in the past and that it is therefore.
A shop applications
