Initially, the shop of Orange applications will be active in France and the United Kingdom.
It will wait until 2010 for that it happens in other countries such as Spain.
Their participation in the Champions League reported 476,4 million to Real Madrid and since its creation
The Champions League has become a source of income for clubs, since its birth in 1992.
Indeed, Real Madrid and the F.C. Barcelona have won 467,4 million, which puts them in third and fifth position of clubs who have earned more money in this competition.
The Manchester United is at the top of the list.
The Manchester United is at the top of the list.
Win the UEFA Champions League does not only the glory. It is also one of the main sources of income of big clubs.
Indeed, the competition has allocated 5 362,5 million euros to 105 teams (including 12 Spanish) who participated in the event since the creation of the tournament, during the 1992-93 season, according to information from UEFA.
The Real Madrid and the F.C. Barcelona have been well served in this division.
The club white was the third of the continent to receive more money for his participation, and the only one, with the A.C. milan, having won the trophy three times.
The Catalan club, current taking the title and last winner of the old European Cup in 1992, is fifth on the list.
At the top of the list are the Manchester United and Bayern Munich, the two teams, billed the more money for their participation in the last Champions League.
And that, although they have lost before the Barça.
On the other hand, Spain is only the third country, as regards money reported by the Champions league, although it has won more titles than any other (five, while Italy has won four, England three and Germany two).
Distribution
This apparent paradox is explained by the complex procedure of distribution of money applied by UEFA.
For this year, the body chaired by Michel Platini expects to earn 1 090 million through the Champions league.
Of this amount, UEFA will million to fixed payments: each of the 20 clubs who participated in the classification matches (including the Atlético de Madrid) received 2.1 million.
In addition, those who have managed to participate have received 3.8 million just to be there, more than 550 00 euros for each match.
There is also a bonus in the event of victory (800,000 euros) and equality (400 000 for each team). Those who come in eighth final of three million each, the eight teams who reach the final quarter of Reçoivent3,3 million.
The last four teams will each receive 4 million.
And the champion will win $9 million, the 5.2 received by the other finalist.
Thus, under fixed payments, a club will win at least 7.1 million, and the maximum 31.2 million.
On the other hand, the barça pocketed 2.5 million for winning the Super Cup in europe in august.
But in addition, there are the variable payments, which are enshrined 337.8 million.
This money is distributed according to the proportional value of each TV market.
The Spanish market is one of the most important, and has four places.
The champion of the previous year gets 40% of the money allocated, 30% for the second, 20% for the third and 10% for the fourth.
The other party will be paid based on the number of matches played during the edition of the year.
Nueva Rumasa provides EUR 61 million to 29.9% of Sos.
The group Nueva Rumasa listed yesterday the details of the offer to purchase of shares by which it intends to acquire a maximum of 25 to 29.9% of the capital of Sos.
A percentage which requires not to launch a takeover bid (opa) for all of the securities.
Specifically, Nueva Rumasa offers 1,5025 euros per share, which will be disbursed in 10 years and who will be paid at a rate of 1% per year for this report.
Yesterday, the shares of Sos have completed 1.85 euros; the supply of Nueva Rumasa therefore assesses the company 18% below the market.
According to Nueva Rumasa, the price of 1.50 euros reflects the real assessment of Sos.
The offer is conditioned by the appointment of eight of the 15 advisers.
The group of Jerez gives a period of 15 days for shareholders to indicate their interest in the sale of securities.
The CNMV assured not having been informed of the offer, although the company of Ruiz Mateos claimed that she had made contact with the regulator.
If it takes place, the disbursement would amount to 611,7 million, while capital of Sos is 254,27 million.
In the meantime, Sos continues the restructuring of its direction.
In an attempt to remain outside any offers to purchase and judicial of its former directors, brothers Jesús and Jaime salazar, it announced the election of María Luis Jordá as director of internal audit.
A decision that in fact the first woman to hold a post leader in the food company.
It is a newly created position that will directly depend on the president of the group.
And it is not free of controversy, as the company remains submerged in the legal battle for the alleged embezzlement of more than 230 million Sos to the Salazar.
Moreover, the possibility that in the coming months Sos reveals new misappropriation of funds cannot be ruled out.
On the credit to Salazar, the former advisers Ildefonso Ortega and Ángel Fernández Noriega (representatives of CCM and Unicaja) said yesterday in the National Audience that they had been informed of the diversion of 212 million without knowing the destination.
