New tools for the expertise of cars
In these days of bad weather and accidents, garages cars are not the only winners.
Every day, thousands of cars that have suffered a disaster are brought up to a garage, where an expert to assess the damage and the cost of repair.
Every disaster is different, and the calculation of the cost of parts and labour time can be a long and complex.
To calculate the cost of a repair of between 20,000 and 30,000 euros, including parts and labour can take two or three hours.
However, with the assistance of the latest computer tools, it would be a matter of minutes.
It is for this reason that almost 100% of experts use such systems.
The suppliers of services and solutions for the assessment of claims and maintenance are dedicated to the collection of information provided by manufacturers, and then treat them and offer their customers in the form of a useful tool.
In Spain, Audatex, the North American group, is the business leader; 80% of the estimates are made with its products.
Other companies in competition in the field of evaluation tools and of the development of information on the sector are GtMotive and Eurotax.
The work with the data provided by manufacturers is far from simple.
According to Eduardo Velázquez, commercial director of Audatex, the company in Spain with 63 manufacturers and importers, and each of them their provides information in a different format.
In addition, the amount of data to treat continues to increase, so that over the past five years, more versions, variations and motors have been launched that over the preceding 15 years.
When a new car lots on the market, these companies are at work.
It is a very hard work, because it is each thousand pieces of the vehicle and include its price.
In addition, it establishes a graphic image "smart" of each model on which you can click on the different parts of a passenger vehicle.
If it is a model sold heavily, the work can be ready in a week if the process progresses very quickly.
If it is a car sold, it can take three or four months. Currently, Audatex provides comprehensive information on 99.2% of cars sold in Spain.
Among the most exclusive models, they have such information on the Porsche, but not the Ferrari or Lamborghini.
On the vehicles in circulation, the figure exceeds the 99%.
To do the work of documentation and databases, Audatex has eight centres across the world (in spain, france, germany, the United states, brazil, mexico, China and japan), and each of them is specialized in certain brands.
The national headquarters is located in Alcobendas (Madrid).
There, more than a hundred technicians (usually experts in mechanical) work simultaneously on three screens of computers.
Audatex invests each year, 90 million to develop these databases.
Each month, 2.5 million data is recorded, and clients receive updates every two days.
The development of this enormous flow of information allows these companies to give them different uses and propose various products.
The most common application for the repair and maintenance, but in different countries, there are also tools for the management of pieces of breaks or to calculate the residual value or a car.
The only company that has a guide that provides information on the value of used cars in Spain is Eurotax.
Audatex suggests not in our country, but it is in the United States.
In view of the products offered by Audatex, it is easy to get an idea of the type of support it can bring to professionals in the sector.
This company offers 10 different tools, the flagship product being AudaPlus, the standard solution assessment, for experts.
There are cars, motorcycles, light and heavy industrial vehicles.
In addition to the cost of parts, it takes into account the repair time estimated by the manufacturer or the scales of paint.
This tool is bought in terms of its use, for each estimate.
The highest cost is 5.75 euros, for customers who use little, the maximum 10 times per month.
Then, each insurance company, which makes thousands of expertise, negotiates its price with Audatex.
Other products, such as AudaVIN, allow the identification of a vehicle and equipment with which he came out of the assembly line, only through its chassis number.
Audaglass focuses on the glasses of vehicles, and AudaSubastas is open to the professional sector server on the Internet to bid on vehicles reported wrecks.
Its statistical service is very useful for identifying trends, analyses géo-démographiques or know the current problems by brand or model.
It is possible to study, for example, how many models of a specific Mark went to the garage for a breakdown or how many had suffered serious losses for a given period.
GT Motive is the only Spanish company dedicated to the development of this type of tools.
It sells, among other things, Gt Estimate, which is also intended to experts and provides digital images, as well as access to documents, price and time records of the manufacturer.
Gt Motive is a company of the group Einsa, founded in 1971, as a provider of services and solutions for the assessment of claims, breakdowns or maintenance devoiture.
The guide GT assessment is a product of historical reference on the market.
The company works with 24 000 users in garages, 3 100 experts and 53 insurance companies.
Its volume of business has increased at a rate of 20% per year over the past three years, and has a turnover of EUR 10.8 million in 2008.
At the beginning of last year, she began the process of internationalisation, with the establishment of an office in paris.
For its part, Audatex was born in Germany in 1966 and is located in Spain in 1979.
According to the sources of the company, 62% of its turnover is done in Europe and in the rest of the world, and the remaining 38% in North and south America. it works with 900 insurance companies and 33 000 garages, including 3 000 are in spain.
The global turnover of the group Solera (Audatex, Sidexa, Informex ABZ, Hollander and IMS) will amount to $557 million, 3.3% more than in 2008.
In our country, the company will receive eur 19.1 million, or 7.2% more than last year.
In 2005, the group Solera was traded for $1 000 million, today, its shares are valued at a total of $400 million.
Since 2007, it is part of the New York Stock Exchange and is part of the benchmark Standard & Poor's.
Internet auction of rugged
Last October, the group has purchased Autoonline, an Internet platform for the sale of cars, motorcycles and special vehicles.
The operation has involved a cost of 59.5 million for 85% of the company's capital, which could expand next year to 15 per cent.
The purpose of the acquisition was to provide more value-added services to its clients, with the possibility of access to a huge international market.
This estimate and sale is intended exclusively for professionals in the sector, such as insurance companies, experts, leasing companies, garages, the scrapyard and sellers professionals who must be registered before starting to conduct operations.
This platform was established in 1996 in Germany and manages more than 650,000 operations across Europe, including 500,000 in Germany.
Among its major markets are Spain, Greece, Poland and Turkey.
There are currently more than 1500 sellers and 4,000 experts registered on the site.
It manages 3,000 announcements by day and on the Spanish market, 100 new announcements are published every day.
Under Spanish law, a car whose chassis number has been withdrawn can no longer move, but on the other hand, some parts which are not damaged can be used as spare parts.
The vintage cars can be re-registered, although they have been withdrawn, after complex approaches.
Garage in four stages
With the tool Auda-taller, the company Audatex ensures that the user obtains a quotation in only four stages: identify the vehicle, the replacement part, create a quotation and generate.
The ease of use is an essential element of these systems, especially to convince the oldest professionals who, to a greater or lesser extent, are reluctant to use of new management techniques.
The database includes 1 034 vehicles, including 666 Tourism, 109, 137 motorcycles, 78 vans and trucks.
Of course, to use a computer and an Internet connection is required.
Once the model to repair identified through its chassis number, a real graphic image of the model in question is then selects the necessary.
The user can include variables such as the price of labour, increases or reductions, then it can print the specifications for the client.
Audataller is not a tool to estimate as AudaPlus, but a catalogue of references.
The main difference between these two systems is that for garages does not include the time of Labour estimated.
The cost of using this tool for the garage is 350 euros per year, which may be the subject of a credit.
Currently, the company Audatex works to ensure that these images are in three dimensions.
It is an innovation that mechanics are a very good eye, as it will, for example, to select a door and turn to see the inside.
